article.headline: Lehigh 65, American 58
article.story: BETHLEHEM, Pa. (AP) -- Jose Olivero scored 21 points -- including 10-of-12 free throw shooting -- to lead Lehigh to a 65-58 victory over American on Saturday. Joe Knight scored 18 points Kyle Neptune had 10 points for Lehigh (14-9, 7-1 Patriot League). Paulius Joneliunas scored a career-high 21 points and Garrison Carr added 13 for American (7-14, 3-5). The two teams were tied for the eighth time, 44-44, with 14:48 remaining when James Anderson hit a pair of baskets to key a 7-0 run that put the Mountain Hawks up 51-44. American got no closer than four points after that. Lehigh hit all six free throw attempts in the final 21 seconds to seal the victory. American jumped out to a 17-0 lead with 8:44 remaining with a 3-pointer by Arvydas Eitutavicius, and a free throw by Joneliunas extended the lead to 10 points with 5:48 remaining in the half. But Lehigh went on a 14-2 run to take a 29-27 lead with 2:05 left in the half, and Olivero hit a pair of free throws with five seconds left to give the Mountain Hawks a 33-32 lead at the half.
